<H3> <TI>   Vice Ministers' Support for Deregulation Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803082494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Mar 
94 Evening Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1803082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa called on 
parliamentary vice ministers to come up with deregulation 
measures and remedies for such exclusionary business practices 
as keiretsu [interlocking corporate groups]. He made the 
remarks at a meeting of parliamentary vice ministers held at the 
second office building for lower house members on 17 March. 
  Hosokawa then stressed his intention to strengthen 
enforcement of the Antimonopoly Law. Also, he called for the 
vice ministers' positive attitudes toward narrowing disparity 
between Japanese and international prices, saying: "I want all 
of you to work on the subject without exceptions because this is 
closely related to the consumers' interests." 

