<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Bomb Destined for Israel Embassy </TI></H3>
<H4>   Envoy Comments </H4>
<F P=102> BK1803040494 Bangkok THE NATION in English 18 Mar 94 p A3 </F>
<F P=103> BK1803040494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE NATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli Ambassador `Uzi Manor said last night he was 
waiting for results of police investigations to establish the 
motive or the possible target of the explosives. He said the 
embassy always takes precautionary measures but Thai police have 
not assigned extra reinforcements to guard the embassy. 
"Reinforcements are at the discretion of the police," he said. 
  The embassy is located in Soi Langsuan. Police suggested 
earlier in the day that the explosives could have been designed 
to avenge the massacre last month at Hebron on the West Bank. 
"But it could be the embassy was selected at random. The 
incident may be connected with the problems in the South. 
Whatever it is, the result could have been a major disaster," 
he added. 
  The embassy has reported the finding of the explosives to 
Jerusalem. "This is standard practice in these circumstances," 
he said. 

</TEXT>

