<H3> <TI>   Deputy Minister: France Ends Import Ban </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1703015494 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 17 Mar 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> BK1703015494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] France has lifted its ban on Thai fishery product 
imports, ending a month-long dispute between the two countries, 
according to official sources. French diplomats in Bangkok would 
not confirm or deny the reports, but Deputy Commerce Minister 
Chaiyot Sasomsap said the French Government had notified its 
Thai counterpart through the Thai Foreign Trade Department that 
Paris would abide by its commitments to allow the imports. The 
source said the Thai Commercial Counselor's office in Paris had 
reported that France would today freely allow the imports to 
enter. 
  A Commerce Ministry source said the ministry could not 
indicate why the process of adding Thailand to the list of 
countries allowed to export fishery produce to France was 
speeded up, after the Thai Government made diplomatic protests 
last week. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

