  By making the exchange abortive, they intend to put a spoke 
in the wheel of DPRK-U.S. talks, hinder the settlement of the 
nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula and slay fellow countrymen 
with the help of foreign sword. 
  The double-faced acts of the "civilian"-veiled warmaniacs, 
who sharpen the sword against fellow countrymen behind the scene 
of dialogue for the exchange of special envoys, are bound to 
face criticism at home and abroad. 
  The nation will never pardon the "civilian"-veiled 
warmaniacs 
