<H3> <TI>   Japan Said Obstructing Nuclear Issue Settlement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1803111094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1053 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1803111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Reckless Act" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 18 (KCNA) -- Japanese Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa told a plenary session of the House 
of Councillors a few days ago that the reexamination of the 
"outline of the defense program" was not aimed at reduction of 
defence forces. 
  Commenting on this, MINJU CHOSON today declares it reveals 
Japan's intention to promote arms buildup and overseas 
aggrandizement more openly. 
  The news analyst says: 
  No country in the world now can match Japan in the growth 
rate of military spendings and the scope of armed forces 
reinforcement. 
  Japan's move to become a military power and arm itself with 
nuclear weapons fully reveals the Japanese reactionaries' wild 
design to build up enough strength to enter into the scrambles 
for world supremacy. 
  They intend to extend the operational scope of the 
"self-defence forces" worldwide and realise their dominationist 
ambition with strength, crying for Japan's "international role 
commensurate with its power." 
  In order to legitimate their dangerous nuclear armament and 
overseas aggrandizement, they are making a fuss about the 
"nuclear issue" of the DPRK. 
  If the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula is resolved 
fundamentally and it becomes a nuclear-free zone, the Japanese 
reactionaries will lose the pretext for turning Japan into a 
military power and promoting its nuclear armament and will be 
unable to stage a comeback to the Korean peninsula, a part of 
their old dream of "the greater East Asia co-prosperity sphere". 
This is why they are creating obstacles to the settlement of 
the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula, hurling mud at the 
DPRK, and are aggravating military confrontation and tension in 
this part of the world. 
  They must know that their reckless act will only precipitate 
their self-destruction. 

</TEXT>

