<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agricultural Development in Unyul County Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1803111194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1007 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1803111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 18 (KCNA) -- The production of 
grain increased 2.1 times, the number of tractors and lorries 
respectively 7 and 6 times, the number of agro-technicians and 
experts 13 times, and the amount of chemical fertilizers applied 
to each hectare 7.4 times in Unyul County, South Hwanghae 
Province. 
  These are achievements made in the county over the past 
thirty years after the publication of the socialist rural theses. 
  The county situated in the central western coast of Korea 
was 
a backward agrarian county in the past. 
  The agriculture of the county began to develop after the 
liberation of the country and made a rapid progress from the 
mid-1960s when the socialist rural theses was published. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song gave on-the-spot 
guidance to work of the Changyon, Wonpyong, Kwanhae and other 
cooperative farms in the county and clearly indicated the 
direction and ways of the county's agricultural development. 
  The county has put big efforts into agricultural irrigation. 
It dammed the Hanil, Kuwang and other rivers and streams to 
build reservoirs, including the Kwanhae and Kuwang reservoirs, 
and set up more than 400 pumping stations and completed a 200 km 
waterway project. Thus, all paddy and non-paddy fields were 
brought under irrigation. 
  The area of the cultivated land increased by hundreds of 
hectares through the reclamation of tideland and acquisition of 
more land. 
  With many dwelling houses, nurseries, kindergartens, 
hospitals, and public welfare and service facilities built in 
the countryside the rural villages have turned into socialist 
cultured ones good to live and work in. 
  At the cooperative farms where comprehensive mechanization 
has reached a stage of completion the farmers joyfully do 
farming with the help of machines. 
  The cooperative farms in the county have sixtyfive farm 
machines of more than 20 kinds each on an average. 
  Each farmer tends 10 hectares of maize fields at the 
Changyon 
and other cooperative farms. 
  Grain production has increased year by year in the county. 
Over 23,000 more tons of grain was produced last year than the 
previous year, countywide. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

