<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Construction of Brick Dwelling Homes Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1703023294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2149 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1703023294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 16 (KCNA) -- A large number of 
silicate brick dwelling houses have been built in Korea. 
  The construction of silicate dwelling houses for sixty 
thousand and several thousand families was undertaken and more 
than fifty thousand flats have been completed in the recent few 
years. 
  As a result, urban-style silicate dwelling houses were built 
in-more than 100 districts and blocks, including Kangan-tong in 
Songyo District, Pyongyang, and Namsinuiju, and the number of 
silicate dwelling houses increased in rural districts. 
  More than 18,000 families moved into new silicate houses 
built in Pyongyang including Kwangbok Street, and thousands of 
families in Namsinuiju. 
  Silicate dwelling houses for ten thousand and several 
thousand families have been built in Sunchon, Pukchang, Anju and 
other coal mining districts. 

</TEXT>

