<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Denies Defense Links With Burma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1703140694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0946 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1703140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Canberra, March 17 (AFP) -- Australia had no 
intention of resuming defence cooperation with Burma until the 
military-ruled nation improved its human rights record, 
Australian Defence Minister Robert Ray said here Thursday. 
  Ray said Australia's re-establishment of accreditation of a 
defence attache did not mean there would be any change in that 
position. 
  Answering a question in parliament, Ray said the attache's 
role was merely to report back on what the Burmese regime and 
its military were doing. 
  "He is not there for defence links between the two 
countries," Ray said. "It's an erroneous view that has been in 
the press. 
  "The Australian government has no intention of resuming 
defence links with Burma. 
  "Given their human rights record, they are certainly not 
deserving of any substantial defence links at this stage. We 
certainly won't be doing such things as defence exports or 
military to military links. 
  "I can guarantee that we will not re-establish the normal 
sort of regional sort of defence relationship with Burma until 
they have a massive improvement in their human rights record." 
  Australian defence cooperation with Burma has been minimal 
and ties were cut entirely in 1991 with the Burmese SLORC [State 
Law and Order Restoration Council] regime's refusal to implement 
democratic reforms. 
  The SLORC military junta seized power in Burma in 1988 after 
blocking the clear winner of national elections, Aung San Suu 
Kyi, from taking power and suppressing the resultant nationwide 
pro- democracy protests. 
  Although Australia has an embassy in Rangoon, the defence 
attache accredited to Burma is based in Bangkok and will make 
occasional visits. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-6490 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas053_q_94002" </HT>


