<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Newspaper Reports Woolsey Remarks on DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1803054694 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO in Korean 18 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> SK1803054694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington--U.S. CIA Director James Woolsey on 17 
March denounced North Korea as one of the states involved 
directly and indirectly in exporting mass lethal weapons and 
terrorism. 
  Appearing on the NBC television network that day, Director 
Woolsey pointed out North Korea, which recently refused a 
full-scale inspection by the International Atomic Energy Agency, 
as being such a state, along with Iran, Iraq, and Libya. 
  He stressed that these two points, including the export of 
terrorism, will possibly impose a serious threat to us, and 
therefore, these points should be dealt with at top priority. 
  Director Woolsey again revealed "the fact that North Korea 
has extracted plutonium capable of manufacturing at least more 
than one nuclear weapon is the view of the majority of U.S. 
intelligence authorities." He said that "there is a possibility 
that North Korea will threaten peace in Northeast Asia and that 
North Korea is a state which proliferates weapons, thus posing a 
serious problem." 

</TEXT>

