<F P=102>  SK1703115094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0717 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1703115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 17 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
said Thursday that he will travel to Russia in the near future 
after visiting Japan and China this month. "Visits to these 
countries are not only for security reasons but also to 
strengthen economic cooperation to beat off the competition," 
Kim told top-grade graduates of 126 universities and their 
parents whom he invited over for lunch. Government officials say 
it is yet to be decided when Kim will visit Russia, but a likely 
date is around June. A European tour timed with his visit to 
Russia is also being considered, they say. 

