<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nguyen Thi Binh on African, French Visits </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1703131994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1703131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Vice President Nguyen Thi Binh by station </F>
correspondent Thanh Hai on her visits to Algeria, Mali, Guinea, 
and Guinea Bissau, and her meeting with French President 
Francois Mitterrand; place and date not given -- recorded] 
  [Summary] Requested by Thanh Hai to outline the general 
purpose of the trip, its overall results as well as particular 
achievements in each of the country she visited, Nguyen Thi Binh 
said that "while we are carrying out the multi-faceted and 
multilateral policy, we should not forget our old friends. The 
primary goal of my trip was to consolidate and promote 
traditional and friendly relations with countries who are our 
long-time friends. The countries I visited are also in the 
process of developing their economies where cooperation and 
solidarity with other countries are essential, so the second 
goal of my trip was to study the possibility of cooperation 
between Vietnam and these countries in economic, trade, 
cultural, and social fields, and to exchange experiences in 
national construction." 
  Nguyen Thi Binh also revealed that she and her delegation 
have made "a number of agreements on economic, trade, cultural, 
science, and technology cooperation. The leaders of the 
countries I visited wanted us to help them in agricultural 
development." 
  She added that the leaders and people of these countries 
understood well the political and economic developments in 
Vietnam. They highly regarded achievements of the Vietnamese 
Government and people in renovating the economy and improving 
ties with the world community. As a representative of Vietnam, 
she was warmly and solemnly welcomed at all the countries she 
visited. The Algerian and Malian governments also conferred 
noble orders on her. 
  Asked to assess the prospects of cooperation between Vietnam 
and these countries in particular and Africa in general, Nguyen 
Thi Binh said presently both Vietnam and the African "friends" 
have limited capital, thus making economic cooperation 
difficult. However, Africa is a "potentially large market for 
Vietnamese agricultural produce and consumer goods" thus 
"promising mutually beneficial cooperation in the future." 
  Asked about her impression on meetings with the French 
President Francois Mitterrand and the ministers of foreign 
affairs and cultural and francophone affairs, Nguyen Thi Binh 
said that although these were only courtesy calls, she had a 
chance to exchange views with French leaders on issues of common 
concern. She said: "The most profound impression I got from 
these meetings was that the ties between Vietnam and the world 
community in general, and France in particular, are constantly 
improving. The French leaders as well as businessmen wish to 
promote cooperation with Vietnam in all fields, which we 
heartily welcome." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

