<F P=102>  BK1503132494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1000 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] The paper CUU CHIEN BINH [WAR VETERAN] today 
carries an article on page two by Bui Dinh Nguyen entitled: 
Opposing Peaceful Evolution -- A Pressing, Significant Task of 
the War Veterans Association [WVA]. 
  The article says: We must strive to foil the peaceful 
evolution scheme in order to firmly maintain the political 
situation; defend our national independence and freedom; build 
the fatherland; and triumphantly fulfill the objectives of 
making our people prosperous, our nation powerful, and our 
society civilized. Opposing peaceful evolution has become a 
very pressing task of our people and the war veterans force. 
Indeed, members of the WVA have actively participated in the 
struggle against peaceful evolution and have, together with 
people throughout the country, strived to heighten vigilance 
against the enemy's schemes and tactics. They have promptly 
detected and consistently monitored work of various 
organizations of reactionaries, especially their sabotage 
activities. Moreover, the WVA has also seriously implemented 
the foreign policy of our party and state, carried out tasks in 
accordance with our party lines and orientations, and motivated 
various people's strata to actively participate in the struggle 
against wicked schemes of the hostile forces. 

