<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Praises IAEA Referral of DPRK Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2103143094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1404 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2103143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government issues a statement in the name of 
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Chang Ki-ho regarding the referral of 
the North Korean nuclear issue to the UN Security Council by the 
International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] special Board of 
Governors meeting. It highly assessed [nopke pyongga] the 
referral, saying this reflected the international community's 
intent. 
  The government urged North Korea to dissolve the 
international community's concerns [kukche sahoeui uryorul 
pulsik sikigo] and to implement its duties by allowing nuclear 
inspections as soon as possible. 
  The government also urged that North Korea join the trend of 
the international community represented by reconciliation and 
cooperation by fulfilling its duty as a signatory of the Nuclear 
Safeguards Accord and by taking steps for easing tensions on the 
Korean peninsula and for building up trust. 

</TEXT>

