<H3> <TI>   North-South Contact Held on 19 Mar in Panmunjom </TI></H3>
<H4>   TV Airs Delegates' Remarks </H4>
<F P=102> SK1903235094 Seoul KBS-1 Television Network in Korean 1200 
GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1903235094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dialogue between Song Yong-tae, chief South Korean delegate </F>
to the working-level contact for the exchange of special envoys 
and Pak Yong-su, his North Korean counterpart, from 
closed-circuit television coverage of the 19 March eighth 
working-level contact in Panmunjon--recorded] 
  [Text] During the North-South working-level contact for 
the special envoy exchange held today, the North Korean side did 
not hesitate to make black-mail-type remarks to the effect that 
it would not decline a war. The following is related footage: 
  [Begin recording] [Pak Yong-su] There is an old-saying that 
fire should be controlled by fire. We do not want war but will 
never shun your side's insisting on a war. We are also ready to 
react [taehang]. However, Mr. Song, your side has to deeply 
consider the dear price of the war. Seoul is not far from here. 
If a war breaks out, it will be a sea of fire. Mr. Song, it 
will probably be difficult for you to survive. 
  [Song Yong-tae] What are you talking about? 
  [Pak] Wait, therefore... 
  [Song] Then, do you think we will just sit back? 
  [Pak] Regarding this, you have to deeply consider things. 
  [Song] Are you declaring a war? 
  [Pak] I am telling you that your side declared a war. Are 
you listening? Did you take a nap? 
  [Song] What? Respond to war with war? 
  [Pak] That's right. Clearly. 
  [Song] Why do you talk about war at the place of talks? 
  [Pak] Because your side declared a war. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

