<H4>   Premier Comments at Cabinet Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> SK2103091994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0913 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2103091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 21 (YONHAP) -- Prime Minister Yi 
Hoe-chang on Monday urged relevant government offices to check 
again their policies toward North Korea and try to strengthen 
the nation's security preparedness flawlessly. 
  "The administration should try to establish a total security 
posture by working out new steps to enhance the people's 
security senses which have somewhat been loosened due to the 
dialogue in the past," Yi said. 
  Yi's press secretary Kang Hyong-sok said the prime minister 
made the remarks while presiding over a cabinet session. 
  Kang quoted the premier as saying that the recent North 
Korean utterances that "we will not hesitate to come to war...," 
serve as an occasion for the South to re-establish the direction 
of its stand toward the South-North dialogue and the nuclear 
issue. 
  Premier Yi also called for detailed plans to ensure 
uninterrupted function of public facilities in emergency. 
  "The prime minister asked the defense and public peace 
authorities to be fully vigilant so that there will be no 
contingency especially during President Kim Yong-sam's upcoming 
visits to Japan and China," Kang said. 

</TEXT>

