<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ozawa, Takemura Compete To Gain JNP Alliance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603055494 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 16 
Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1603055494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 16 March Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Ichiro Ozawa, secretary general of Shinseito [Japan 
Renewal Party], had dinner with Hirotaro Yamazaki, chairman of 
the Japan New Party [JNP] general conference of Diet members of 
both houses, and seven other JNP Diet members at a hotel in 
Tokyo on the evening of 15 March. He exchanged views with them 
on the realignment of the political world. 
  According to a participant in the gathering, Ozawa said: 
"Prime Minister Hosokawa is a great man who knows his 
priorities. The JNP should also be confident in its support of 
the administration." 
  Also present at this meeting were Diet members Toshio 
Yamaguchi and Naoto Kitamura. Ozawa had also met with other JNP 
Diet members on 7 and 10 March. 
  On the other hand, Chief Cabinet Secretary Masayoshi 
Takemura 
(head of Sakigake [Harbinger]) attended a study group of 
Sakigake and JNP members on information and communications on 
the morning of 15 March. He said in his speech, "While I will 
not attend the general meeting of Sakigake Diet members, I 
intend to deal actively with party affairs," thus impressing his 
listeners with his enthusiasm for party affairs. 
  Because Ozawa has been actively approaching JNP Diet 
members, 
Takemura apparently feels that it is not enough for him to 
"concentrate on administrative affairs." The tug-of-war between 
the two men to form an alliance with the JNP is expected to grow 
in intensity. 

</TEXT>

