<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rengo To Establish Policy Consultative Organ </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703033294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 16 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1703033294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Japan Trade Union Confederation [Rengo], at its 
senior executives meeting on 15 March, decided to soon establish 
the "Rengo political forum" (tentative name), the policy 
consultative organ composed of Diet members from various parties 
including conservatives. Among those parties are the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], the Democratic Socialist Party 
[DSP], Sakigake [Harbinger], and the Japan New Party. 
  Within Rengo, moves toward the political realignment have 
been observed. For example, the All-Japan Prefectural and 
Municipal Workers Union, the Japan Teachers Union, the Japan 
Electric Communications Union [as published], and the Japan 
Postal Workers Union have agreed to provide financial assistance 
and electoral cooperation so as to unite the SDPJ, the DSP, and 
liberal forces. The purpose of this organ is to create grounds 
for unifying a new force by engaging in policy coordination 
between various parties. 
  At Rengo's Central Committee session scheduled for 17 March, 
Chairman Akira Yamagishi will officially propose the 
establishment of the organ. Then, members of both the SDPJ and 
the DSP and some intellectuals will form a preparatory team in 
early April to work on establishing the new organ. 

</TEXT>

