<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Explains Drop in Support Rate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2103055794 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 20 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2103055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yushi Kanemoto] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 19 Mar -- Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa 
held a meeting in Beijing with reporters traveling with him on 
his China trip on the evening of 19 March. Touching on the 
first drop in the cabinet's support rate below 50 percent as 
indicated in the two opinion polls conducted by the JNN [Japan 
News Network] data bank, composed of such agencies as the TBS 
[Tokyo Broadcasting System] and by the JIJI News Agency, 
Hosokawa said: "It must have been affected by such troubles as 
the National Welfare Tax and the cabinet reshuffle. Also, the 
rice issue (concerning the shortage of rice at stores). Various 
factors are involved." Then, he continued to say: "I have no 
other choice but to carry on without paying much attention to 
this. I believe what I am supposed to do is to pay attention to 
what I am doing now." 

</TEXT>

