<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Parties Boycott Parliament Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803184394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1737 GMT 18 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1803184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 18 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The spring 
session of the State Great Hural (SGH), which started its work 
three days ago, is sitting without participation of the 
representatives of the opposition. Six members of the 
Parliament, representing the coalition of the Mongolian National 
Democratic Party and the Mongolian Social Democratic Party, have 
stopped participating in work of the spring session of the State 
Great Hural. On Wednesday [16 March] they announced that they 
would not participate in the session till the Parliament 
discusses the initiatives of the president of Mongolia, which he 
has put forward in his speech at the opening of the SGH session, 
and adopts a corresponding decision on them. 
  The State Great Hural Standing Committee on Hurals and 
Administration has considered as expedient to submit for 
consideration to the present session of the Parliament the 
president's proposal on elaboration of the draft law on 
elections to the State Great Hural, on making amendments and 
additions in the Law on State Great Hural in a new fashion. But 
the Parliament has not accepted the president's draft resolution 
concerning ensuring the guarantees of work on propaganda of 
activity of the State Great Hural through the state mass media. 

</TEXT>

