<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Supporters Hold Antigovernment Rally </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803185394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1733 GMT 18 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1803185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 18 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Today on 
the square "Erh Choloo" ("Freedom") of the Mongolian capital a 
mass rally was organized by the Mongolian Democratic Union 
(MDU). At the meeting present were the leader of the Mongolian 
Social Democratic Party (MSDP) B. Batbayar, the General 
Secretary of the Mongolian National Democratic Party E. Bat-uul, 
one of the leaders of the Mongolian Democratic Union T. 
Enhtubshin, the Chairman of the Union of Mongolian Students B. 
Erdenetsogt, the representatives of the MDU in province. 
Thousands of people gathered at the meeting. In their hands 
there were posters "democracy is not anarchy", "down with the 
government", "mafia of functionaries is dividing the country". 
They were blaming the government, the Parliament and its 
leaders for corruption, abuse of power, blockading freedom of 
press, the issuing of laws not meeting the requirements of the 
people and were demanding the present government to resign. 
  As the General Secretary of the Mongolian National 
Democratic 
Party E. Bat-uul announced, if the government and the Parliament 
do not meet the demands of the opposition and the president, so 
it will recall its members from the Parliament, and will 
continue to struggle in the most resolute way. 

</TEXT>

