<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leaders Consider Hural Participation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803194994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1717 GMT 18 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1803194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 18 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Five 
representatives of the oppositional parties of the country have 
decided to resume their participation in the activities of the 
Great State Hural if proposals forwarded by the president of the 
country at the opening ceremony of the autumn session of the 
Parliament would be accepted by the Parliament. 
  Such a statement was made at the press conference by a 
member 
of the Great State Hural R. Gonchigdorj. He noted that the 
opposition in the Great State Hural are fighting not for power 
but in the interests of particular strata of the Mongolian 
public. According to him, the opposition parties would not 
abandon their democratic principles standing for the creation of 
a state structure to be acting in the interests of the whole 
people of Mongolia. 

</TEXT>

