<H3> <TI>   Anwar To Deliver Election Campaign Promises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1903082694 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1903082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Malay </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Datuk Sri Anwar Ibrahim, deputy prime minister, 
today pledged to the people of Sabah that the Barisan Nasional, 
BN, Government will deliver on the promises it made during state 
elections campaigns. He said that this would include the 
introduction of a rotation system for the appointment of any 
leader to the state chief minister's post, and to set up a 
university in Sabah. 
  Datuk Sri Anwar, who is now in Honolulu to attend the 
meeting 
of Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation, APEC, finance ministers, 
has extended his congratulations to Tan Sri Sakaran Dandai, 
chairman of the Sabah BN, on his appointment as new chief 
minister of Sabah. 
  The deputy prime minister also expressed the hope that the 
new state government in Sabah would not fail to achieve its goal 
to set up a clean and just administration. 

