<H3> <TI>   Mahathir Hopes `New Era Will Emerge' in Sabah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103095594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2103095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed hopes 
that that a new era will emerge in Sabah following the formation 
of the National Front Government in the state last week. He 
said the new era can be brought about considering that the 
appointment of Tan Sri Sakaran Dandai as the new Sabah chief 
minister be well accepted by all sides in the state. [sentence 
as heard] He told reporters this when asked about the setting up 
of the new Sabah cabinet. 
  He had earlier launched the book: THE MAKING OF THE NATIONAL 
CAR -- NOT JUST A DREAM. Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir said the number 
of members in the Sabah cabinet had yet to be determined and 
that the matter would be discussed at the meeting of the 
National Front Supreme Council to be held in Kuala Lumpur 
tomorrow night. 

