<H3> <TI>   Government Troops Occupy Khmer Rouge Base </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1903130294 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1903130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Communique of the General Staff of the Khmer Royal Armed </F>
Forces"; dated 19 March -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] To ensure public security and stability throughout 
the Kingdom of Cambodia and in order to correctly implement the 
policy of the Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia which 
does not allow the existence of secessionist areas or division 
of area under separate administration, the General Staff would 
like to report that the Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF] have 
been forced to completely occupy [chol kan kap] the area that is 
the largest position [ti tang thom bamphot] of the Khmer Rouge 
rebels at 1800 on 19 March. 
  With the assistance of the KRAF forces stationed there, 
efforts are being made to normalize the situation. The General 
Staff will provide detailed information later. 
  [Signed] The General Staff of the KRAF 
  [Dated] 19 March 1994 

</TEXT>

