<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japan Denounced for `Comfort Women' Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903103994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1903103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["International Justice Will Not Pardon Japan's Crime" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- If the Japanese 
Government authorities continue to resort to petty tricks to 
evade the responsibility for the criminal drafting of "comfort 
women for the Army", the world public will never pardon the 
crimes of Japan which gravely violated the international law and 
international morality, warns NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined 
article today. 
  It says: 
  Though the criminal drafting of "comfort women" was 
committed 
long ago, it is not a problem of the past but of today because 
the truth of the crime and its culprits have been confirmed in 
recent years. 
  Japan must honestly admit this crime, apologize for it and 
make compensations. 
  The Japanese authorities are evading the responsibility 
under 
the international law and ridiculously argue that the demand of 
the victims for compensations has already been settled through 
bilateral and multilateral agreements. 
  The international law defining war crimes and "crimes 
against 
humanity" demands compensations to the victims and punishment of 
those responsible. It is a crafty ruse to dodge punishment at 
any cost for Japan to persist in its attempt to evade the 
responsibility under the international law. 
  The Japanese Government has no legal right to rescind the 
human rights of an individual. The demand for a compensation is 
a right of the victims whose human rights were abused. 
  The Japanese authorities are nowadays even foolishly 
claiming 
it is impossible to verify that the victims demanding 
compensations were really "comfort women". This reveals their 
moral inferiority. They are lost to elementary human conscience 
and morality. If those responsible are not punished, Japan must 
be brought to the international court. 
  The Japanese authorities must admit at an earlier date the 
responsibility under the international law for the crime of 
Japan in drafting "comfort women for the Army" and seek its 
solution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

