<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Leaders Praise Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903103894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1000 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1903103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- The general secretary 
of the Egyptian National Democratic Party, Youssef Amin Wali, 
when he received the Korean ambassador on March 10, said 
respected His Excellency President Kim Il-song is a world-famous 
statesman, an outstanding leader and a true leader of the people. 
  He said the dear leader His Excellency Kim Chong-il is a 
great man who is wisely leading the party, the state and the 
Army of Korea and noted the agreement reached at a recent 
contact between the DPRK and the U.S. is a fruition of his 
distinguished strategy. 
  The chairman of the Nepal Workers and Peasants Party, 
Narayan 
Man Bijukchhe, when he received the Korean ambassador on March 
8, said the letter sent by the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song 
to the National Agricultural Conference indicates the most 
correct way of the ultimate solution of the rural question under 
socialism. 
  All the lines and policies put forward by Comrade Kim 
Il-song, he noted, serve as the genuine guideline of party 
activities. 
  The general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal 
Communist Party (United Marxism-Leninism), Madhav Kumar Nepal, 
received the Korean ambassador on March 9 and told him that 
Korea continues giving full play to the superiority of socialism 
because its people have respected Comrade Kim Il-song and dear 
Comrade Kim Chong-il as their great leaders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

