<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Replies to Foreign Party Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1803125694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1045 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1803125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [All names as received] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 18 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent messages to foreign party leaders in 
reply to their messages of greetings on the occasion of his 
birthday. 
  Among them are Chea Sim, chairman of the Central Committee 
of 
the People's Party of Cambodia and speaker of the parliament of 
the Kingdom of Cambodia; Madhav Kumar Nepal, general secretary 
of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United 
Marxism-Leninism); Narayan Man Bijukchhe, chairman of the Nepal 
Workers and Peasants Party; Samboram Shrestha, secretary general 
of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist League; Walid 
Joumblatt, president of the Socialist Progressive Party of 
Lebanon; Chairman Inaam Raad and General Secretary of the 
Supreme Council Ali Hassan of the Nationalist Socialist Party of 
Syria in Lebanon; Farouk Dahrouj, general secretary of the 
Central Committee of the Lebanese Communist Party; Abdallah al 
Chahal, secretary of the Lebanese Regional Leadership of the 
Arab Socialist Baath Party; Budragchagiyn Dashyondon, general 
secretary of the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party; Dogu 
Ferincek, chairman of the Workers' Party of Turkey; Rafiq Ahmad 
Sheikh, secretary general of the Pakistan People's Party; C.R. 
Aslam, president of the Pakistan Socialist Party; Iqbal Ahmed 
Khan, secretary general of the Pakistan Muslim League; Vassos 
Lyssarides, chairman of the Socialist Party of Cyprus; Yacob 
Zayadine, general secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Jordanian Communist Party; Talal Hafun Ala Mai, general 
secretary of the People's Unity Party (Unionist) of Jordan; 
Indrajit Gupta, general secretary of the National Council of the 
Communist Party of India; Youssef Amin Wali, general secretary 
of the Egyptian National Democratic Party; Milud al Mahdabi, 
general secretary of the Permanent Secretariat of the 
Organization of Socialists in the Mediterranean; Roland 
Atta-Kesson, national chairman of the National Convention Party 
of Ghana; Huudu Yahaya, general secretary of the National 
Democratic Congress of Ghana; I.B.A. Kelepha Samba, national 
president of the People's Progressive Party of Gambia; El Hadj 
Boubacar Diallo, general secretary of the Party for Unity and 
Progress of Guinea; Ngirumpatse Mathieu, president of the 
National Republican Movement for the Democracy and Development 
of Rwanda; Mamadou El Bechir Gologo, secretary general of the 
National Direction Committee of the Sudanese Union-African 
Democratic Rally in Mali; Mohamedoun Dicko, secretary general of 
the Executive Committee of the African Party for the Solidarity 
and Justice of Mali; Nicolas Mayugi, chairman of the Central 
Committee of the Burundi Party of Unity for National Progress; 
Toe De Stanislas, general secretary of the Democratic Youth 
Revolutionary Party of Burkina Faso; Ali Houdou, secretary 
general of the Party of Revolution of Benin; Leonel Mario Da 
Alva, chairman of the Democratic Convergence Party and Reflexion 
Group of Sao Tome and Principe; Carlos Dias Da Graca, general 
secretary of the Liberation Movement-Social Democratic Party of 
Sao Tome and Principe; Emile Kibala Bey A Nsien, national 
chairman of the Workers' Party of Zaire; Otete Gaston Mboyo, 
national chairman of the National Movement of the Genuine 
Lumumbist Combatants of Zaire; Lambert Mende Omalanga, national 
chairman of the Lumumba Congolese National Movement-Original of 
