<H3> <TI>   WPK Delegation Returns From Vietnam, Laos </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903054294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1903054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the Workers Party of Korea [WPK] 
led by WPK Secretary Hwang Chang-yop returned home by train on 
17 March from a visit to Vietnam and Laos. 
  Receiving the delegation at Pyongyang station were Kim 
Yang-kon, deputy director of the WPK Central Committee; Duong 
Chinh Thuc, ambassador of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam to 
our country; and Qiao Zonghuai, PRC ambassador. 
  The delegation left Vientiane on 13 March after winding up 
its Laos visit. At the airport, Thongsing Thammavong, member of 
the Political Bureau of the Central Committee and chairman of 
the Party Organization Committee of the Lao People's 
Revolutionary Party, other functionaries concerned, and our 
country's ambassador to Laos saw the delegation off. 

</TEXT>

