<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Thanks Troops Working in Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903044694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0420 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1903044694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- Comrade Kim Chong-il, 
supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, sent thanks to 
the soldiers of the Yo Chong-ku, Chang Song-chun, Kim Son-tu, 
Han Chae-son and Kang Sang-sop units of the Korean People's Army 
who had set examples in assisting the countryside. 
  Commanding officers and soldiers of the units have 
contributed to the impelementation of the party's 
agriculture-first policy by sending large quantities of aid 
materials to cooperative farms and transporting their goods this 
year and deepened the feelings of army-people unity, looking 
after the life of the families of fallen soldiers and servicemen. 

</TEXT>

