<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Yi In-mo's Return Celebrated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903050794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0428 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1903050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pyongyangites Greet 1st Anniversary of Yi In-mo's Return </F>
Home" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- Working people in 
Pyongyang held a joint meeting to mark the first anniversary of 
the return of a former war correspondent of the Korean People's 
Army Yi In-mo, to the bosom of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
  Put up at the meeting place was a board carrying the words 
of 
the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il: "Our party remembers 
Comrade Yi In-mo, an incarnation of faith and will". On display 
at the meeting place were silk banners, scrolls and gifts sent 
by people of all strata to Yi In-mo. 
  Kim Ki-nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea, in his speech at the meeting said that 
Yi In-mo's return to the socialist homeland with an unshakable 
faith and will for the party and the leader was a historical 
event which demonstrated the brilliant victory of Korean-style 
socialism centred on the popular masses over capitalism. 
  "Yi In-mo could fight resolutely with an unshakable faith in 
the party and the leader, unflinchingly defending the principle 
of a member of the Workers' Party of Korea, not yielding to the 
sufferings in prison for 34 years in South Korea, because he 
revered the great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il, the mental pillars of the Korean 
people, the speaker said, and stressed: 
  "Through Yi's destiny, the Korean people have become more 
convinced and keenly felt that the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il is the destiny of our country and nation, the destiny 
of socialism and a great symbol of all our victory, glory and 
happiness". 
  Yi In-mo said that it is the dear leader who has brought him 
back to life from the jaw of death and extended warm thanks to 
the dear leader who has brought him the happiness today. He 
said he came to the meeting with a floral basket, wishing the 
great leader President Kim Il-song and general Kim Chong-il a 
long life in good health. 
  Yi Hyon-ok, daughter of Yi In-mo, referring to the loving 
care shown by the dear leader to her father, said that the dear 
leader is the destiny and a tender-hearted father of all our 
people. 
  Yi In-mo and his family sang a song overflowing with deepest 
reverence for the dear leader to the accompaniment of the piano 
sent by him. 
  Poems written by Yi In-mo in praise of the greatness of 
general Kim Chong-il were read at the meeting. 
  Anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters and workers, farmers, 
youths and students of the new generation present at the meeting 
said that they would defend and glorify Korean-style socialism, 
loudly singing the song of faith that we would certainly win in 
any difficulty because we are guided by supreme commander 
general Kim Chong-il. 
  Gifts from people of all strata to Yi In-mo were conveyed at 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

