<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Yi In-mo's Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1903104894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1024 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1903104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Great Love That Had Made Dead Tree Blossom" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- It is the day when Yi 
In-mo well known at home and abroad as the incarnation of faith 
and will came back to the socialist homeland a year ago. 
  His 365 days in the homeland were really impressive days 
embroidered with the noble love and obligation and the 
unbreakable bonds of kinship between the illustrious leader and 
an ordinary soldier. 
  The 43 years of Yi In-mo in a "hell on earth" and his one 
year in the earthly paradise make us picture to ourselves the 
incarnation of great human love that has made a dead tree 
blossom. 
  Yi In-mo served as a war correspondent in the period of the 
fatherland liberation war unleashed by the U.S. imperialists 40 
odd years ago. During the war, he got heavily wounded and was 
taken prisoner, leaving his fate unknown. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song awarded a certificate 
of the bereaved family of a revolutionary martyr to Yi In-mo's 
family in 1968 when his fate was not known, expressing 
unquestioned trust in the soldier. 
  After it was known that he was alive and he fought 
undauntedly for 34 years in prison, the great leader, very 
pleased that his trust in him was not in vain, decided to confer 
the title of the Hero of the Republic upon him, highly 
appreciating his patriotic faith and will. 
  Immeasurable are the efforts exerted by him to bring an old 
soldier on sickbed at a tip of South Korea back to Pyongyang 
where his wife and a daughter were waiting for him. 
  At the time he was sent back to the North, he was, indeed, a 
"dead man." His internal organs were all abnormal and he was 
suffering from serious malnutrition, pyothorax and general 
famine by medieval tortures for more than 12,400 days in prison. 
  Even officials concerned of the South wondered if he could 
reach Pyongyang alive. 
  Yi In-mo, however, expressed his admiration for the 
fascinating reality of the North three days after he was 
embraced by the Republic and began writing some 70 days after. 
It was some 100 days after he returned to the North that he 
left the sickbed and toured different places of the socialist 
homeland together with his family, seeing its imposing reality 
at first hand. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il have always shown deep loving care for his 
health and life over the last one year. More than 100 kinds of 
tonics and expensive medicine sent by them for his health and 
their precious teachings on more than 120 occasions and deep 
love on over 40 occasions have brought him to the culmination of 
happiness and glory. 
  Yi In-mo has visited time-honored Mangyongdae, Mt. Paektu, 
the ancestral mountain, the Tower of the Chuche Idea, the arch 
of triumph, Pabal-ri, his home town, and other places of the 
homeland. 
  Touring the homeland, he has keenly felt that the love and 
trust of the illustrious leader is not confined to him but 
reaches all of the people. 
  Therefore, he, out of the absolute worship to the 
illustrious 
leader, wrote poems "On My Fate," "Thought of Love" and "Song in 
Praise of Faith and Will" and words of the song "We Will Win 
Because You Are Leading Us" and other works singing of the noble 
love of the Workers' Party of Korea, and today contributed a 
full-length article titled "We Are Blessed With Sagacious 
Leader" to NODONG SINMUN. 
  This is not only what Yi In-mo said from the bottom of his 
heart but the unshakable faith of the entire Korean people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

