<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Note on Aid Signed With SRV </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2103073794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0701 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2103073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 21 KYODO -- Japan and Vietnam on 
Monday [21 March] signed a diplomatic note in Hanoi for a 
Japanese grant of 3 billion yen, the Foreign Ministry said. 
  The grant will be provided as part of Japan's international 
commitment made at the 1992 Munich summit of the world's seven 
leading economic powers, which promised grant money to 
developing countries, the ministry said. The grant is the first 
of its kind to Vietnam and will be used to help Vietnam pay for 
purchases of foreign goods. 

