Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 17 KYODO -- The Finance Ministry said 
Thursday [17 March] it will raise the base interest rate on 
loans from its fund management bureau to government institutions 
by 0.65 percentage point to 4.30 percent per annum. 
  Following the move, the government-backed Housing Loan Corp. 
is expected to raise its base housing loan rate from the record 
low 3.6 percent per annum to around 4.0 percent, probably 
effective late April. 
  The Fund Management Bureau, which invests public funds from 
postal savings and other sources, offers the loans to the 
Housing Loan Corp., Japan Road Corp. and other government-backed 
organizations. 
  The base housing loan rate applies to loans for houses with 
a 
floor space of up to 125 square meters. 

