<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 19 -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai this afternoon left Ho Chi Minh City, concluding his 
four-day official visit to Vietnam. 
  While in Ho Chi Minh City, the Thai prime minister and his 
party was warmly received by President Le Duc Anh. Chairman of 
the People's Committee of Ho Chi Minh City Truong Tan Sang gave 
a banquet in honour of the Thai prime minister and his party. 
During the meeting, Chairman Truong Tan Sang stated that the 
