<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge Claims Two T-54 Tanks Destroyed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1903125694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1903125694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Battle Report from Pailin Battlefield on 16 and 17 March"] </F>
  [Text] 1. On 16 March, troops of the two-headed 
government continued to proceed along Route 10, Phnum Veng, and 
Kamping Puoy. On Route 10 and south of the Phnum Veng fronts, 
they were routed by our forces; over 20 bodies were left on the 
battlefield and a number of other soldiers were wounded. On the 
Kamping Puoy front, they were also routed by our forces; over 10 
bodies were left on the battlefield and some other soldiers were 
wounded. 
  2. On 17 March, on the Phnum Veng front, we routed and 
destroyed two T-54 tanks on the spot. 

</TEXT>

